The paper deals with information theory, specifically mutual information and relative entropy, in the context of a Poisson channel. This suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses estimation and filtering, which are topics in machine learning and control theory, respectively, indicating that cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions stochastic processes, which are studied in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), making it a less likely but still possible sub-category.
